**Module 1: Define the factorial function**  
The function `factorial` will compute the factorial of a non-negative integer `x`.  
```javascript
function factorial(x) {
  if (x < 0) {
    throw new Error("x must be a non-negative integer");
  }
  let result = 1;
  for (let i = 2; i <= x; i++) {
    result *= i;
  }
  return result;
}
```

